e.co.uk/awards/2016/orchestral Orchestral 2016]</ref>\n*Special Achievement \u2013 [[BBC Radio 3]]\n*Young Artist of the Year \u2013 [[Benjamin Appl]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2016/young-artist-of-the-year|title=Young Artist of the Year|date=15 September 2016|website=www.gramophone.co.uk}}</ref>\n*Baroque Instrumental \u2013 ''Biber Rosary Sonatas'', [[Rachel Podger]] violin with [[Jonathan Manson]] violoncello, [[viol]] David Miller archlute [[Marcin Swiatkiewicz]] harps, organ<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2016/baroque-instrumental|title=Baroque Instrumental|date=22 August 2016|website=www.gramophone.co.uk}}</ref>\n*Baroque Vocal \u2013 [[Claudio Monteverdi|Monteverdi]], ''Madrigali, Vol 1 \u2013 Cremona'' \u2013 [[Les Arts Florissants (ensemble)|Les Arts Florissants]] / [[Paul Agnew]]\n*Chamber \u2013 Tippett String Quartets [[Heath Quartet]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2016/chamber|title=Chamber|date=22 August 2016|website=www.gramophone.co.uk}}</ref>\n*Choral \u2013 [[Arnold Schoenberg|Schoenberg]] ''[[Gurrelieder]]'' \u2013 [[Barbara Haveman]] soprano [[Claudia Mahnke]] mez [[Brandon Jovanovich]], [[Gerhard Siegel]] tenors Thomas Bauer baritone [[Johannes Martin Kr\u00e4nzle]] spkr Netherlands Female Youth Choir; Cologne Cathedral Choir, Male Voices and Vocal Ensemble; Chorus of the Bach-Verein, Cologne; Kart\u00e4userkantorei, Cologne; Cologne G\u00fcrzenich Orchestra / [[Markus Stenz]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2016/choral|title=Choral|date=22 August 2016|website=www.gramophone.co.uk}}</ref>\n*Concerto \u2013 [[Benjamin Britten|Britten]]. Korngold Violin Concertos \u2013 [[Vilde Frang]] violin [[Frankfurt Radio Symphony Orchestra]] / [[James Gaffigan (conductor)|James Gaffigan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2016/concerto|title=Concerto|date=22 August 2016|website=www.gramophone.co.uk}}</ref>\n*Contemporary \u2013 [[Hans Abrahams