i Rautavaara|Rautavaara]]: [[Incantations (composition)|Percussion Concerto]], Cello Concerto No 2, ''Modificata'', [[Colin Currie]] (percussion) [[Truls M\u00f8rk]] (cello) [[Helsinki Philharmonic Orchestra]] / [[John Storg\u00e5rds]] ([[Ondine (record label)|Ondine]])\n*Chamber &ndash; [[Robert Schumann|Schumann]]: Complete works for piano trio, [[Christian Tetzlaff]] (violin) Tanja Tetzlaff (cello) [[Leif Ove Andsnes]] (piano) (EMI)\n\n===2011===\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Gustavo Dudamel]], conductor\n*Specialist Classical Chart &ndash; [[Milo\u0161 Karadagli\u0107]] \u2013 The Guitar\n*Label of the Year &ndash; [[Wigmore Hall Live]]\n*Young Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Milo\u0161 Karadagli\u0107]]\n*Special Achievement &ndash; The [[Bach Cantata Pilgrimage]] on [[Soli Deo Gloria (record label)|SDG]]\n*Lifetime Achievement &ndash; Dame [[Janet Baker]], mezzo-soprano\n*Music in the Community Award &ndash; [[The Cobweb Orchestra]]\n*Baroque Instrumental &ndash; [[Carl Philipp Emanuel Bach|CPE Bach]] ''Harpsichord Concertos'' [[Andreas Staier]]; [[Freiburg Baroque]] / [[Petra M\u00fcllejans]] [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Baroque Vocal &ndash; [[Handel]] ''[[Apollo e Dafne (Handel)|Apollo e Dafne]]'' La Risonanza Glossa\n*Chamber (Record of the Year) &ndash; [[Dvo\u0159\u00e1k]] ''String Quartets Op. 106 & 96'' [[Pavel Haas Quartet]] Supraphon\n*Choral &ndash; [[Edward Elgar|Elgar]] ''The Kingdom'' [[Claire Rutter]]; [[Susan Bickley]]; [[John Hudson (singer)|John Hudson]]; [[Iain Paterson (bass-baritone)|Iain Paterson]]; [[Hall\u00e9 Choir & Orchestra]] / Sir [[Mark Elder]]\n*Concerto &ndash; [[Claude Debussy|Debussy]] ''Fantaisie'' [[Ravel]] ''Piano Concertos'' [[Massenet]] ''Piano works'' [[Jean-Efflam Bavouzet]]; [[BBC Symphony Orchestra]] / [[Yan Pascal Tortelier]] Chandos\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Harrison Birtwistle|Birtwistle]] ''Night's Black Bird'' [[Hall\u00e9 Orchestra]] / [[Ryan Wigglesworth]] NMC\n*DVD Documentary &ndash; [[Carlos Kleiber]]: ''Traces to Nowhere'' A film by [[Eric Schultz]] Arthaus\n*DVD Performance &ndash; [[Giuseppe Verdi|Verdi]] ''[[Don Carlo]]'' Soloists; Chorus and Orchestra of the Royal Opera House, Covent Garden / [[Antonio Pappano]] EMI Classics\n*Early Music &ndash; [[Striggio]] ''Mass in 40 Parts etc.'' I Fagiolini ''et al.'' / [[Robert Hollingworth]] Decca\n*Historic &ndash; [[Gustav Mahler|Mahler]]/Cooke ''Symphony No 10'' [[London Symphony Orchestra]], Philharmonia / [[Berthold Goldschmidt]]\n*Instrumental &ndash; [[Brahms]] ''Handel Variations. Piano works, Op 118 & 119'' [[Murray Perahia]] Sony Classical\n*Opera &ndash; [[Rossini]] ''[[Ermione]]'' Soloists; [[Geoffrey Mitchell Choir]]; [[London Philharmonic Orchestra]] / [[David Parry (conductor)|David Parry]] Opera Rara\n*Orchestral &ndash; [[Shostakovich]] ''Symphony No 10'' RLPO / [[Vasily Petrenko]] Naxos\n*Recital &ndash; [[Verismo Arias]] Various [[Jonas Kaufmann]]; Chorus and Orchestra of the Santa Cecilia Academy, Rome / [[Antonio Pappano]] Decca Classics\n*Solo vocal &ndash; [[Benjamin Britten|Britten]] ''[[Songs and Proverbs of William Blake]]'' [[Gerald Finley]]; [[Julius Drake]] Hyperion\n*Editor's Choice &ndash; [[Rossini]] ''[[Stabat Mater (Rossini)|Stabat Mater]]'' Netrebko; [[Orchestra dell'Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia|Santa Cecilia Orchestra]] & Choir / [[Antonio Pappano]] EMI\n\n===2010===\n[http://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/gramophone-awards-2010-unveiled Complete list]\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Joyce DiDonato]]\n*Lifetime Achievement Award &ndash; [[Alfred Brendel]]\n*Young Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Sol Gabetta]]\n*Label of the Year &ndash; [[Linn Records]]\n*Early Music (Record of the Year) &ndash; Byrd 'Infelix Ego' / [[The Cardinall's Musick]] and [[Andrew Carwood]]\n*Baroque Instrumental &ndash; [[Vivaldi]] The French Connection / [[La Serenissima (musical ensemble)|La Serenissima]]\n*Chamber &ndash; [[Beethoven]], Sonatas for Piano and Violin / [[Isabelle Faust]]\n*Concerto &ndash;