y Music &ndash; [[Guillaume Dufay]], Missa Jacobi, Binchois Consort/Kirkman ([[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]])\n*Contemporary &ndash; Toru Takemitsu, Quotation of Dream, Knussen ([[Deutsche Grammophon|DG]])\n*Instrumental &ndash; [[Arcadi Volodos]], Arcadi Volodos Live at Carnegie Hall ([[Sony Classical]])\n*Orchestral &ndash; [[Anton Bruckner]], Symphony No. 4, Wand (RCA)\n*Recital &ndash; [[Ren\u00e9e Fleming]], ''I Want Magic!'', [[Ren\u00e9e Fleming]]; [[James Levine|Levine]] ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n*Solo Vocal &ndash; [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], Lieder, Stephen Genz; Vignoles (Hyperion)\n*20th-Century Chamber &ndash; Elliott Carter, String Quartets, Arditti Quartett (Auvidis)\n*20th-Century Instrumental &ndash; [[Luciano Berio]], Sequenzas, various artists ([[Deutsche Grammophon|DG]])\n*20th-Century Opera &ndash; [[Carl Nielsen]], Maskarade, Schirmer ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n*20th-Century Orchestral &ndash; Edgar Var\u00e8se, Complete Orchestral Works, Riccardo Chailly (Decca)\n*20th-Century Vocal &ndash; Hanns Eisler, Hollywood Songbook, Goerne; Schneider ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n\n===1998===\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Riccardo Chailly]]\n*Lifetime Achievement &ndash; Menahem Pressler\n*Choral (Record of the Year) &ndash; Martin, Pizzetti, Die Sch\u00f6pfung, Westminster Cathedral Choir/[[James O'Donnell (organist)|James O'Donnell]] ([[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]])\n*Best-selling disc &ndash; [[James Horner]], Titanic&ndash;Original Soundtrack (Sony Classical)\n*Editor's Choice &ndash; [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s]], Ad\u00e8s: Arcadiana Op. 12. The origin of the harp, soloists; [[Endellion Quartet]]; [[London Sinfonietta]]; [[King's college choir]], Cambridge/Ad\u00e8s, Stenz, Cleobury (EMI Debut)\n*Baroque Non-Vocal &ndash; Les Talens Lyriques/Christophe Rousset, Rameau&mdash;Overtures (L'Oiseau-Lyre)\n*Baroque Vocal &ndash; [[Claudio Monteverdi|Monteverdi]], [[Concerto Italiano]], Rinaldo Alessandrini\n*Chamber &ndash; Bart\u00f3k, String quartets, Takacs Quar