c-fm-gramophone-awards |title=Gramophone Awards 2015 &#124; Nominations, Winners & Performers |publisher=Classic FM |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> They are often viewed as equivalent to<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.classicfm.com/radio/shows/david-mellor/gramophone-awards-2012/ |title=Gramophone Awards 2012 Special &#124; Radio Shows |publisher=Classic FM |date=2012-09-20 |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> or surpassing<ref>{{cite web|author=Anastasia Tsioulcas|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/deceptivecadence/2013/08/27/215749389/slimmed-down-gramophone-awards-honor-home-team|title=Slimmed-Down Gramophone Awards Honor Home Team|publisher=[[NPR]] Classical|date=2013-08-27|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Anastasia Tsioulcas|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/deceptivecadence/2011/10/06/141110545/the-gramophone-awards-2011-what-do-you-think|title=The Gramophone Awards 2011: What Do You Think?|publisher=[[NPR]] Classical|date=6 October 2011|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref> the American [[Grammy Award|Grammy award]], and referred to as the ''[[Academy Awards|Oscars]]'' for [[classical music]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Mike Wade|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/uk/scotland/article2748607.ece|title=Classical 'Oscar' for Scots label|newspaper=The Times|date=2010-09-30|accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.albion-media.com/clients/gramophone-awards |title=Gramophone Awards |publisher=Albion Media |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820200812/http://www.albion-media.com/clients/gramophone-awards/ |archive-date=20 August 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccaclassics.com/gb/gpp/index/deccaclassics-gramophone |title=Decca \u2013 home of classical music |publisher=Deccaclassics.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> They are widely regarded as the most influential and prestigious classical music awards in the world.<ref>{{cite web|author=Charlotte Smith |url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2013-announced |title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2013 announced! |publisher=gramophone.co.uk |date=2013-09-17 |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.joshuabell.com/awards |title=Awards \u2013 The Official Joshua Bell Site |publisher=Joshuabell.com |date=2008-04-07 |accessdate=2016-08-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819082249/http://www.joshuabell.com/awards/ |archivedate=19 August 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> According to Matthew Owen, national sales manager for [[Harmonia Mundi]] USA, \"ultimately it is the classical award, especially worldwide.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=John Henken|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/sns-grammys-gramophone-story.html#page=1|title=Gramophone Awards: Where classical is the star|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=19 February 2001|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\nThe winners are selected annually by [[critic]]s for the ''[[Gramophone (magazine)|''Gramophone'']]'' magazine and various members of the industry, including retailers, broadcasters, arts administrators, and musicians. Awards are usually presented in September each year in London.\n\n==Gramophone Awards of the 2010s==\n\n=== 2019<ref>[https://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/article/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2019-the-winners-revealed Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2019: the winners revealed!], ''Gramophone''</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/article/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2019-the-full-report|title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2019: the full report|website=Gramophone|language=en|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref> ===\n\n*Lifetime Achievement: [[Emma Kirkby]]\n*Orchestra of the Year: [[Hong Kong Philharmonic Orchestra]]\n*Artist of the Year: [[V\u00edkingur \u00d3lafsson]]\n*Young Artist of the Year: [[Jakub J\u00f3zef Orli\u0144ski]]\n*Label of the Year: [[Pentatone (record 