-Century Vocal &ndash; Hanns Eisler, Hollywood Songbook, Goerne; Schneider ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n\n===1998===\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Riccardo Chailly]]\n*Lifetime Achievement &ndash; Menahem Pressler\n*Choral (Record of the Year) &ndash; Martin, Pizzetti, Die Sch\u00f6pfung, Westminster Cathedral Choir/[[James O'Donnell (organist)|James O'Donnell]] ([[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]])\n*Best-selling disc &ndash; [[James Horner]], Titanic&ndash;Original Soundtrack (Sony Classical)\n*Editor's Choice &ndash; [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s]], Ad\u00e8s: Arcadiana Op. 12. The origin of the harp, soloists; [[Endellion Quartet]]; [[London Sinfonietta]]; [[King's college choir]], Cambridge/Ad\u00e8s, Stenz, Cleobury (EMI Debut)\n*Baroque Non-Vocal &ndash; Les Talens Lyriques/Christophe Rousset, Rameau&mdash;Overtures (L'Oiseau-Lyre)\n*Baroque Vocal &ndash; [[Claudio Monteverdi|Monteverdi]], [[Concerto Italiano]], Rinaldo Alessandrini\n*Chamber &ndash; Bart\u00f3k, String quartets, Takacs Quartet (Decca)\n*Concerto &ndash; Joshua Bell, Barber, Bloch, Walton, Baltimore Symphony Orchestra/David Zinman ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Harrison Birtwistle|Birtwistle]] The Mask of Orpheus, Andrew Davis, Martyn Brabbins, Birtwistle, soloists; BBC Singers; [[BBC Symphony Orchestra]]/[[Andrew Davis (conductor)|Andrew Davis]], Martyn Brabbins (NMC)\n*Early Music &ndash; Canciones and Ensaladas, Ensemble Cl\u00e9ment Janequin/Dominique Visse (Harmonia Mundi)\n*Early Opera &ndash; [[Jean-Philippe Rameau|Rameau]], Les f\u00eates d'H\u00e9b\u00e9, Soloists; Les Arts Florissants Chorus and Orchestra/William Christie (Erato)\n*Film Music &ndash; Kenneth Alwyn, The Ladykillers, Royal Ballet Sinfonia/Kenneth Alwyn (Silva Screen)\n*Instrumental &ndash; Stephen Hough, Mompou ([[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]])\n*Music Theatre &ndash; Kander & Ebb, Chicago, Broadway Cast/Rob Fisher (RCA Victor)\n*Opera &ndash; [[Gioacchino Rossini|Rossini]], ''Il Turco in Italia'', soloists; Milan L