and series#Complete list of available songs|downloadable song for Rock Band]].<ref>[http://www.rockband.com/songs/wakingthedemon Waking the Demon by Bullet For My Valentine // Songs // Rock Band\u00ae<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=December 2019}}\nThe video is about a teenage [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] fan that gets bullied in high school by a jock. The leader of the group is dating a girl who seems sympathetic for the boy, but is not brave enough to stand up for him. There are numerous shots of the band playing in a moonlit forest. Throughout the video, the jock repeatedly attacks the boy, including spraying warm showers on him in the locker room and dumping a Strawberry shake on him in class, tripping him, pushing him into walls, smacking him with a towel, splashing bathroom water on his face, etc. Meanwhile, the teenager crosses off dates on a calendar in his locker. He circles the last date, the 28th, which is labeled, \"Full Moon\".  That night, he watches the jocks' leader who bullied him, waiting by the forest for his girlfriend who lured him to the forest by asking to meet him there so that the teenage boy could get revenge on him. The teenager throws a balloon filled with cottage cheese at the jock's car to provoke him to chase him deeper into the forest. The song prepares for the solo as the jock chases the boy through the forest.  As the guitar solo starts, the teenager falls down on his knees and the full moon comes out of the clouds, turning him into a werewolf. The bully approaches the now changed boy. Once the jock sees the teenage victim's face, the jock is horrified and tries to run, and is presumably killed by the werewolf. Blood drips from the werewolf's mouth and hands, and the next day at school, there is a new sign displaying the original bully as missing. Now another jock tries to show his anger towards the victim and tries to harass him a little bit. The girl from the old bully runs up and hugs him, hinting that now she's going out with him after news that the leader went missing. As the other jock walks off with the girl, she looks at the teenager, giving him a look of \"I'm on your side\" and he sees her eyes glow red (revealing that she also is a werewolf like himself). He smiles knowing that her new \"boyfriend\" will be the next victim, and crosses out the first day of the next month waiting for the full moon to come again, implying that the new jock won't be able to harass him so easily.\n\n==Track listing==\n;iTunes Single <ref>{{cite web|title = iTunes Store: Waking The Demon - Single|url = https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/waking-the-demon-single/id278685568 | publisher = [[Apple Inc.]] |date = 26 April 2008 | accessdate = 16 March 2010 }}</ref>\n# \"Waking the Demon\" \u2013 4:07\n# \"Say Goodnight\" (acoustic version) \u2013 3:14\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Bullet for My Valentine'''\n*Matthew \"Matt\" Tuck{{snd}}lead vocals, rhythm guitar\n*Jason \"Jay\" James{{snd}}bass guitar, backing vocals\n*Michael \"Padge\" Paget{{snd}}lead guitar\n*Michael \"Moose\" Thomas{{snd}}drums, percussion\n\n'''Production'''\n*Produced by [[Colin Richardson]]\n*Music video directed by Max Nicols\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Country\n! Date\n! Format\n|-\n| United States\n| 21 April 2008\n| CD single\n|-\n| United Kingdom\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 16 June 2008\n| iTunes\n|-\n| Japan\n|rowspan=\"2\"|EP\n|-\n| South Korea\n|}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart \n! Peak Chart Position\n|-\n| U.S. [[Mainstream Rock Tracks]]\n|align=\"center\"| 39\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|bullet-for-my-valentine|waking-the-demon}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q2I0ulTZWXA Official Music Video]\n{{Bullet for My Valentine}}\n\n[[Category:2008 singles]]\n[[Category:Bullet for My Valentine songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Matthew Tuck]]\n[[Category:200