avirus.html |title=A Drop in TV Ratings for a Democratic Debate Praised for Its Substance |work=[[The New York Times]] |author= Michael M. Grynbaum |date=March 16, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| CNN studio<br />[[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=\"CNNmar12\">{{cite web |title=Democratic debate moved from Arizona to Washington, DC, over coronavirus concerns, DNC announces |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/12/politics/cnn-univision-debate-arizona-dc/index.html |website=[[CNN]] |accessdate=March 12, 2020 |date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n| [[CNN]]<br />[[Univision]]<br />[[Congressional Hispanic Caucus]] BOLD<!-- \"BOLD\" is not a formatting mistake.  It is part of the name. -->\n| [[Dana Bash]]<br />[[Ilia Calder\u00f3n]]<br />[[Jake Tapper]]<ref name=\"CNNmar12\"/>\n|}\n\n=== Participation ===\nThe following is a table of participating candidates in each debate:\n<!--ALPHABETICAL ORDER, THEN BY REVERSE ORDER OF WHEN THEY DROPPED OUT-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;margin:auto\"\n|+Participating candidates in the DNC-sanctioned debates<ref name=\"PoliticoDraw1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/14/dnc-announces-first-debate-lineups-1365570 |title=DNC, NBC announce first debate lineups |last1=Montellaro |first1=Zach |last2=Cadelago |first2=Christopher |date=June 14, 2019 |work=Politico |access-date=June 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"cnndraw\">{{cite web |url=https://www.axios.com/cnn-sets-lineups-second-round-democratic-debates-ec329450-0cef-4d16-8d43-64f003cac9f2.html |title=CNN sets lineups for second round of Democratic debates |author=Orion Rummler |date=July 18, 2019 |publisher=[[Axios (website)|Axios]]}}</ref><ref name=\"sept12d\">{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/final-lineup-set-sole-night-abc-democratic-primary/story?id=65241916 |title=Final lineup set for sole night of ABC Democratic primary debate |last=Karson |first=Kendall |date=August 29, 2019 |work=[[ABC News]] |url-status=live |access-da