rk Post]] |access-date=June 7, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"auto15\">{{cite tweet |last=Rauh |first=Grace |user=gracerauh |number=1130612168263700480 |title=Mayor de Blasio is one step closer to the debate stage. He tells @errollouis he scored 1% in 3 qualifying polls, which is required. \"On that measure we have sort of gotten to first base,\" de Blasio said. Campaign initially had been uncertain that a recent Reuters poll counted. |date=May 20, 2019 |access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NewQualStatus\" />\n|-\n| [[John Delaney (Maryland politician)|Delaney]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}<br />{{small|({{sort|01.0|1.0}}%, 3 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Eric Swalwell|Swalwell]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}<br />{{small|({{sort|01.0|1.0}}%, 3 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Bullock]]\n| {{no}}\n|{{No|No|align=|style=|color=}}<br />{{small|(2 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{no}}\n| <ref name=\"DebatesQual538Bullock\">{{cite web |url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/how-steve-bullock-could-win-the-2020-democratic-primary/ |title=How Steve Bullock Could Win The 2020 Democratic Primary (updated June 6) |last=Rakich |first=Nathaniel |date=June 6, 2019 |publisher=[[FiveThirtyEight|538]] |access-date=June 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NewQualStatus\" />\n|-\n| [[Wayne Messam|Messam]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}<br />{{small|(1 qualifying poll)}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Mike Gravel|Gravel]]\n| {{no}}<br />{{small|(40,000 donors on June 1)}}\n| {{no}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"GravelDebateQualification\">{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/mike-gravel-says-he-hopes-to-make-it-to-dem-presidential-debate-stage |title=Mike Gravel says he hopes to make it to Dem presidential debate stage |last=Halaschak |first=Zachary |date=April 22, 2019 |website=[[Washington Examiner]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423002926/https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/mike-gravel-says-he-hopes-to-make