emocratic-primary-debates-tracking-qualifications-polling-fundraising/index.html |title=Here's who has qualified for the Democratic primary debates |last=Wright |first=David |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 14, 2019 |date=June 14, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT fundraising\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/08/02/us/politics/2020-democratic-fundraising.html |title=Detailed Maps of the Donors Powering the 2020 Democratic Campaigns |work=New York Times |access-date=August 5, 2019 |date=August 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Bullock]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"auto\" /><ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n|[[Bill de Blasio|de Blasio]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n| [[John Delaney (Maryland politician)|Delaney]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"auto\" /><ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n| [[Wayne Messam|Messam]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"auto\" />\n|-\n| [[Tim Ryan (Ohio politician)|Ryan]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"ryan-fundraising\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cleveland.com/politics/2019/07/tim-ryan-raises-895k-for-presidential-bid-significantly-trailing-rivals.html |title=Tim Ryan raises $895k for presidential bid, significantly trailing rivals |author=Seth A. Richardson |date=July 12, 2019 |website=[[Cleveland.com]] |access-date=August 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Joe Sestak|Sestak]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n|\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Jay Inslee|Inslee]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(on August 19)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref>{{cite tweet |date=August 19, 2019 |access-date=August 20, 2019 |number=1163628395961257984 |user=JayInslee |title=We did it. 130,000 donors rallying behind our #ClimateMission. |last=Inslee |first=Jay}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Kirsten Gillibrand|Gillibrand]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(1 qualifying poll)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://kirstengillibrand.com/ |title=Brave wins |access-date=August 22, 2019 |publisher=Kirsten Gillibrand}}</ref><ref name=\"politico8aug \"/>\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| | [[John Hickenlooper|Hickenlooper]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(1 qualifying poll)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"Hick13\" />\n|-  style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Mike Gravel|Gravel]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"GravelDonorCount \"/>\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Seth Moulton|Moulton]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{no}}\n| <ref name=\"auto\" /><ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" class=\"table-no\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{legend|#f0e68c|Withdrawn candidate}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Summary ====\n{{Infobox debate\n|name          = Democratic Party debates\n|image         = \n|order         = Third Democratic debate\n|host          = [[ABC News]]<br />[[Univision]]\n|date          = September 12, 2019\n|venue         = [[Health and Physical Education Arena|Health&nbsp;&&nbsp;Physical&nbsp;Education&nbsp;Arena]]<br />[[Texas Southern University]]\n|location      = [[Houston]], [[Texas]]\n|leadmoderator = [[George Stephanopoulos]]\n|othermoderators = [[David Muir]]<br />Linsey Davis<br />[[Jorge Ramos (news anchor)|Jorge Ramos]]\n}}\n{{external media\n| float  = right\n| topic  = ABC News/Univision Democratic Debate, <br />Houston, Texas, September 12, 2019\n| video1 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2UWVO0Trd1c Live Stream Recording], <br />[[ABC News]] ''via [[YouTube]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2UWVO0Trd1c |title=ABC News Democratic Debate \u2013 WATCH THE FULL DEBATE (2019) |access-date=2020-02-25 |via=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n| video2 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5KhSJd44qC4 Live Stream Recording], <br />[[Univision]] ''via [[YouTube]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5KhSJd44qC4 |title=En Vivo y En Espa\u00f1ol: 10 precandidatos dem\u00f3cratas participan en el tercer debate dem\u00f3crata |access-date=2020-02-25 |via=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe '''Democratic Party's third presidential debate''' ahead of the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]] took place on September 12, 2019 in [[Houston]], [[Texas]].\n\nIt aired on [[ABC News]] and [[Univision]]. [[George Stephanopoulos]] was the lead moderator of the debate, joined by [[David Muir]], Linsey Davis, and [[Jorge Ramos (news anchor)|Jorge Ramos]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/abc-news-announces-details-democratic-primary-debate/story?id=65077321 |title=ABC News announces details for 3rd Democratic primary debate |author=Kendall Karson |date=August 21, 2019 |work=[[ABC News]] |access-date=August 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe candidates who qualified for the third debate were Biden, Booker, Buttigieg, Castro, Harris, Klobuchar, O'Rourke, Sanders, Warren, and Yang.<ref name=\"sept12d \"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display:inline-table;line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! Candidates\n!Airtime (min.)<ref name=\"third debate talking time\">{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2019/politics/who-spoke-most-at-democratic-debate-september/ |title=Who talked the most during the third Democratic debate |date=September 12, 2019 |work=Washington Post}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Joe Biden|Biden]]\n|17.4\n|-\n|[[Elizabeth Warren|Warren]]\n|16.5\n|-\n|[[Cory Booker|Booker]]\n|14.7\n|-\n|[[Bernie Sanders|Sanders]]\n|14.1\n|-\n|[[Kamala Harris|Harris]]\n|13.7\n|-\n|[[Pete Buttigieg|Buttigieg]]\n|11.4\n|-\n|[[Julian Castro|Castro]]\n|11.0\n|-\n|[[Amy Klobuchar|Klobuchar]]\n|10.4\n|-\n|[[Beto O'Rourke|O'Rourke]]\n|9.3\n|-\n|[[Andrew Yang|Yang]]\n|7.9\n|-\n|'''Average'''\n|'''12.6'''\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n=== Fourth debate (October 15, 2019) ===\n\n==== Qualification ====\nA memo released by the DNC on August 5 indicated that the qualification period for the fourth debate in October started on June 28, which was the same day that qualification began for the third debate (in effect allowing all candidates who qualified for the third debate to automatically qualify for the fourth debate). This gave candidates who did not qualify for the September debate more time to qualify for the October debate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/08/06/dnc-2020-democratic-debate-1448871 |title=DNC rules could expand, not shrink, future debate stage |author=Zach Montellaro |date=August 6, 2019 |work=[[Politico]] |access-date=August 6, 2019}}</ref> Biden, Booker, Buttigieg, Castro, Harris, Klobuchar, O'Rourke, Sanders, Warren, and Yang qualified before August 22,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/08/22/2020-candidates-face-a-critical-debate-deadline-heres-what-happens-if-they-miss-it.html |title=2020 candidates face a critical debate deadline. Here's what happens if they miss it |author=Jordan McDonald |date=August 22, 2019 |work=[[NBC News]] |access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref> while Steyer and Gabbard qualified on September 8<ref name=\"politicosept8\">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/09/08/tom-steyer-2020-democrats-debates-1485202 |title=Tom Steyer qualifies for October debate |last=Montellaro |first=Zach |date=September 8, 2019 |publisher=Politico |access-date=September 8, 2019}}</ref> and September 24 respectively.<ref name=\"nytsept24\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/24/us/politics/tulsi-gabbard-debate.html |title=Tulsi Gabbard Qualifies for Next Debate, Bringing Lineup to 12 |last=Stevens |first=Matt |date=September 24, 2019 |website=[[The New York Times]] |language=en |access-date=September 24, 2019}}</ref> The qualification deadline for the fourth debate was October 1, 2019.<ref name=\"poctd\">{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/08/31/october-democratic-primary-debate-dates-announced-1479435 |title=Fourth Democratic debate scheduled for mid-October |work=[[Politico]] |date=August 31, 2019 |access-date=August 31, 2019 |author=Zach Montellaro}}</ref> One candidate (de Blasio) suspended his campaign between the third and fourth debates.<ref name=\"db\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/think/opinion/why-i-m-ending-my-2020-presidential-campaign-what-i-ncna1056761 |title=Mayor Bill de Blasio: Why I'm ending my 2020 presidential campaign |website=NBC News |language=en |access-date=September 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\";\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\" |Qualification requirements for the fourth debate\n|-\n|'''Polling criterion'''\n|A candidate needed to get at '''least two percent support''' in '''four different polls''' published from a list of approved pollsters between June 28 and October 1, which cannot be based on open-ended questions and may cover either the national level or one of the first four primary/caucus states (Iowa, New Hampshire, Nevada, and South Carolina). Only one poll from each approved pollster counted towards meeting the criterion in each region. The approved pollsters were the [[Associated Press]], [[ABC News]], [[CBS News]], [[CNN]], ''[[The Des Moines Register]]'', [[Fox News]], [[Monmouth University Polling Institute|Monmouth University]], [[National Public Radio]], [[NBC News]], ''[[The New York Times]]'', [[Quinnipiac University Polling Institute|Quinnipiac University]], the [[University of New Hampshire]], ''[[USA Today]]'', ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', ''[[The Washington Post]]'', and [[Winthrop University]].\n|-\n|'''Fundraising criterion'''\n|Before the deadline, 11:59&nbsp;p.m. on October 1, a candidate needed to receive financial support from a minimum of 130,000 unique donors, with at least 400 unique donors per state in at least 20 states.\n|}\n\n<!--Table has presorted the candidates by this order:\n(1) All criteria met.\n(2) Polling criterion met.\n(3) Donor criterion met.\n(4) No criteria met.\n* and they are further presorted within these 4 categories by polling average & polls-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:95%;line-height:16px;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\"|'''Qualified candidates for the fourth debate'''\n|-\n! Candidate\n! Met donor criterion<br />\n! Met polling criterion<br />{{small|(as of October 1)<ref name=\"PollingData3and4\" />}}\n! Met both criteria<br />\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Additional<br />Ref(s)\n|-\n| [[Joe Biden|Biden]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-06-18}}<br />{{small|(before June 18)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes|Yes|align=|style=|color=}}\n| <ref name=\"CNN\" /><ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Pete Buttigieg|Buttigieg]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-06-14}}<br />{{small|(before June 14)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes|Yes|align=|style=|color=}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Kamala Harris|Harris]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-06-14}}<br />{{small|(before June 14)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes|Yes|align=|style=|color=}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Bernie Sanders|Sanders]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-06-14}}<br />{{small|(before June 14)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes|Yes|align=|style=|color=}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Elizabeth Warren|Warren]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-06-14}}<br />{{small|(before June 14)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes|Yes|align=|style=|color=}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Cory Booker|Booker]]\n| {{Yes}}{{Hs|2019-07-29}}<br