nn-jake-tapper-dana-bash-don-lemon |title=3 CNN correspondents will moderate the second Democratic debate |website=Vox |last1=Zhou |first1=Li |date=July 30, 2019 |access-date=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! 2B\n| July 31, 2019<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/02/politics/cnn-2020-democratic-debate-july-detroit/index.html |title=CNN's 2020 Democratic debate set for July 30-31 in Detroit |last1=Cole |first1=Devan |date=April 2, 2019 |access-date=May 13, 2019 |publisher=CNN}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 8\u201310:30&nbsp;p.m.\n| ~13.8 million <br /> (10.7m live TV; 3.1m streaming)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/08/01/democratic-debates-viewers-july-1444440 |title=Night 2 of Detroit Dem debates drew 10.7 million viewers, well below June ratings |author=Quint Forgey |date=August 1, 2019 |access-date=January 20, 2020 |publisher=[[Politico]]}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2020 Democratic Party presidential debates#Third debate (September 12, 2019)|3]]\n| September 12, 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |8\u201311 p.m.\n| 14.04 million live TV<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/democratic-debate-scores-tv-ratings-thursday-sept-12-2019-1239467 |title=TV Ratings: Third Democratic Debate Scores Big |last1=Porter |first1=Rick |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=September 13, 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"1\" |[[Health and Physical Education Arena]],<br />[[Texas Southern University]],<br />[[Houston]], Texas<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/houston-texas/houston/article/TSU-selected-as-site-of-September-Democratic-14112195.php |title=TSU selected as site of September Democratic primary debate |author=Zach Despart |date=July 21, 2019 |work=[[Houston Chronicle]] |access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"1\" |[[ABC News]]<br />[[Univision]]\n| rowspan=\"1\" |Linsey Davis<br />[[David Muir]]<br />[[Jorge Ramos (news anchor)|Jorge Ramos]]<br />[[George Stephanopou