 Democratic presidential debate |website=[[CBS News]] |language=en-US |author=Grace Segers, Caroline Cournoyer, Kathryn Watson |access-date=December 18, 2019 |date=December 17, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"politicojan11\">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/01/11/january-debate-candidates-097505 |title=Next debate stage will be the smallest, whitest one yet |website=[[Politico]] |language=en-US |access-date=January 11, 2020 |date=January 11, 2020 |author=Zach Montellaro}}</ref><ref name=\"Eighthlineup\">{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/candidates-qualify-hampshire-democratic-primary-debate-podium-order/story?id=68796457 |title=7 candidates qualify for New Hampshire Democratic primary debate, podium order and format announced |author=Quinn Scanlan |date=February 7, 2020 |access-date=February 7, 2020 |work=[[ABC News]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Ninthlineup\">{{cite web |last1=Quinn |first1=Melissa |title=Who has qualified for the Nevada Democratic debate so far |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/democratic-debate-nevada-qualify-candidates/ |website=CBS News |access-date=February 20, 2020 |date=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n! rowspan=\"3\"|Candidate\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;\" class=\"table-no\"|\n{{small|{{color box|#90FF90|P}} Present\n{{color box|#FFFFDD|A}} Absent\n{{color box|#CCFFCC|I}} Invited\n{{color box|#FF9090|N}} Not invited\n{{color box|#ececec|Out}} Not yet entered race\n{{color box|#f0e68c|W}} Withdrawn}}\n<!-- Use debate-cell templates: {{D-P}}, {{D-A}}, {{D-I}}, {{D-N}}, {{D-Out}}, {{D-W}}. Sorting numbers for each of the templates goes up from 0 to 4, omitting {{D-A}}. So, {{D-P}} is 0, {{D-I}} is 1, {{D-N}} is 2, etc-->\n|-\n! [[#First debates (June 26\u201327, 2019)|1]]||[[#Second debates (July 30\u201331, 2019)|2]]||[[#Third debate (September 12, 2019)|3]] || [[#Fourth debate (October 15, 2019)|4]] || [[#Fifth debate (November 20, 2019)|5]] || [[#Sixth debate (December 19, 2019