| {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || colspan=7 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Beto|O'Rourke|Beto O'Rourke 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || colspan=8 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Tim|Ryan|Tim Ryan 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || colspan=8 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Bill|de Blasio|Bill de Blasio 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || colspan=9 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Kirsten|Gillibrand|Kirsten Gillibrand 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || colspan=10 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Seth|Moulton|Seth Moulton 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || colspan=10 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Jay|Inslee|Jay Inslee 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}}|| colspan=10 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|John|Hickenlooper|John Hickenlooper 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || colspan=10 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Mike|Gravel|Mike Gravel 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || {{sort|2|{{D-N}}}} || colspan=10 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Eric|Swalwell|Eric Swalwell 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| {{sort|0|{{D-P}}}} || colspan=11 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|-\n! nowrap style=\"text-align:left\" | {{sortname|Richard|Ojeda|Richard Ojeda 2020 presidential campaign}}\n| colspan=12 {{sort|4|{{D-W}}}}\n|}\n\n== Debates in 2019 ==\n\n=== First debates (June 26\u201327, 2019) ===\n\n==== Qualification ====\nTo qualify for the first debates, entrants had to, at a minimum, achieve one of the two criteria listed. If this had resulted in more than 20 qualified candidates, the two criteria would have been evaluated in combination per an outlined set of [[tiebreaker|tiebreaking rules]], but since 20 candidates qualified, no tiebreaker was necessary.<ref name=\"DNC-qualify\">{{cite web |url=https://democrats.org/press/dnc-announces-details-for-the-first-two-presidential-primary-debates/ |title=DNC Announces Details For The First Two Presidential Primary Debates (February 14, 2019) |date=May 9, 2019 |publisher=Democratic National Committee |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510160522/https://democrats.org/press/dnc-announces-details-for-the-first-two-presidential-primary-debates/ |archive-date=May 10, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=May 9, 2019}}</ref> The deadline for candidates to meet either of the below criteria was June 12.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-set-tiebreakers-for-candidates-to-qualify-for-2020-debates-11557444460 |title=Democrats Set Tiebreakers for Candidates to Qualify for 2020 Debates |last1=Thomas |first1=Ken |date=May 9, 2019 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |access-date=May 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509234945/https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-set-tiebreakers-for-candidates-to-qualify-for-2020-debates-11557444460 |archive-date=May 9, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"PerezVideo\">{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1X8eOrqa_Lw |title=DNC chair on gun violence: I fear things will never change |date=June 1, 2019 |people=Tom Perez interview at CNN |access-date=June 4, 2019 |via=YouTube |medium=YouTube video}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\";\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\" |Qualification requirements for the first debate\n|-\n|'''Polling criterion'''\n|Attain at least 1% support in a minimum of 3 approved polls at a national level or in the first four primary/caucus states (Iowa, New Hampshire, Nevada, and South Carolina). The polling threshold was determined using only the published top-line result (whether or not it was a rounded or weighted number) of polls published between January 1, 2019 and June 12, 2019, with each candidate only having been able to count one poll by the same pollster within each region towards the requirement. For a poll to be considered it must not have been based on open-ended questions,<ref name=\"NewQualStatus\">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/06/democratic-debates-2020-election-1356115 |title=Who's in \u2014 and out \u2014 of the first Democratic debates |last=Montellaro |first=Zach |date=June 6, 2019 |website=[[Politico]] |access-date=June 6, 2019}}</ref> and also needed to have been commissioned or conducted by a limited set of organizations: the [[Associated Press]], [[ABC News]], [[CBS News]], [[CNN]], ''[[The Des Moines Register]]'', [[Fox News]], the ''[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]'', [[Monmouth University Polling Institute|Monmouth University]], [[National Public Radio]], [[NBC News]], ''[[The New York Times]]'', [[Quinnipiac University Polling Institute|Quinnipiac University]], [[Reuters]], the [[University of New Hampshire]], ''[[USA Today]]'', ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', ''[[The Washington Post]]'', and [[Winthrop University]].\n|-\n|'''Fundraising criterion'''\n|Meet a fundraising threshold, in which a candidate must have received donations from a minimum of 65,000 unique donors, with at least 200 unique donors per state in at least 20 states. Candidates who wished to qualify using the fundraising threshold must have presented evidence to the DNC of their eligibility using donor data collected by [[ActBlue]] or [[NGP VAN]].\n|}\n\n<!--Table has presorted the candidates by this order:\n(1) All criteria met.\n(2) Polling criterion met.\n(3) Donor criterion met.\n(4) No criteria met.\nand they are further presorted within these categories by polling average & polls-->{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:95%;line-height:16px;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\"| '''Qualified candidates for the first debate'''<ref name=\"DebatesQualCNN\">{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/05/09/politics/democratic-primary-debates-tracking-qualifications-polling-fundraising/index.html? |title=Here's who has qualified for the Democratic primary debates |last=Wright |first=David |date=June 4, 2019 |publisher=[[CNN]] |orig-year=May 9, 2019 |access-date=June 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"DebatesQual538\">{{cite web |url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/the-democratic-debate-lineup-gets-shuffled-and-some-good-news-for-mike-gravel/ |title=The Bottom Of The Democratic Field Is Making Moves, Too |first1=Nathaniel |last1=Rakich |first2=Geoffrey |last2=Skelley |date=June 6, 2019 |publisher=[[FiveThirtyEight|538]] |access-date=June 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"DebatesQualABC\">{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/20-presidential-candidates-qualify-democratic-national-committee-debates/story?id=63479889 |title=20 presidential candidates qualify for first Democratic National Committee debates, reaching limit |last=Karson |first=Kendall |date=June 10, 2019 |publisher=[[ABC News]] |access-date=June 10, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"DebatesQualHill\">{{cite web |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/445318-whip-list-which-2020-dems-are-assured-a-spot-on-the-primary-debate-stage |title=Whip list: Who's clinched a spot in the 2020 Democratic debates (updated June 10) |last=Axelrod |first=Tal |date=June 10, 2019 |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |access-date=June 10, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"DebateQualPolitico\"