\" /><ref name=\"HillJuly30\" /><ref name=\"auto37\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/sep/29/cory-booker-2020-race-funding-goals |title=Cory Booker may quit 2020 race by Tuesday despite 'avalanche of support' |last=Martin Pengelly |publisher=The Guardian |access-date=September 29, 2019 |date=September 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Julian Castro|Castro]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by September 23)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"castro-qualifies\" /><ref name=\"HillJuly30\" /><ref name=\"auto36\">{{cite tweet |user=TrackerDebate |number=1175457989991575553 |title=Donor update: A @JulianCastro fundraising email says he is \"inches\" away from 175K donors |last=The Debate Tracker |publisher=The Debate Tracker on Twitter |access-date=September 23, 2019 |date=September 21, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Marianne Williamson|Williamson]]\n| {{No}}<br />{{nowrap|{{small|(~140,000 donors on October 4)}}}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"auto34\">{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/warren-surpasses-biden-latest-fundraising-haul-falls-short/story?id=65978063 |title=Warren surpasses Biden in latest fundraising hall but falls short of Sanders |first1=Soo Rin |last1=Kim |first2=Kendall |last2=Karson |publisher=ABC News |date=October 4, 2019 |access-date=October 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Michael Bennet|Bennet]]\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(~28,000 donors on June 30)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n| [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Bullock]]\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(~17,000 donors on June 30)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n| [[John Delaney (Maryland politician)|Delaney]]\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(~8,000 donors on June 30)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"NYT fundraising\" />\n|-\n|[[Joe Sestak|Sestak]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n|\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Beto O'Rourke|O'Rourke]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(before June 30)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(2 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|3.5}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"nytimes_map\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/08/02/us/politics/2020-democratic-fundraising.html |title=Detailed Maps of the Donors Powering the 2020 Democratic Campaigns |first=Josh |last=Katz |work=New York Times |access-date=September 23, 2019 |date=June 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Tim Ryan (Ohio politician)|Ryan]]\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(~13,000 donors on July 12)}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n| <ref name=\"ryan-fundraising\" />\n|- style=\"background:#f0e68c;\"\n| [[Wayne Messam|Messam]]\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}} {{hs|0}}\n| {{No}}<br />{{small|(0 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{No}}\n|\n|-\n| colspan=6 class=\"table-no\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{legend|#f0e68c|Withdrawn candidate}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Summary ====\n{{Infobox debate\n|name          = Democratic Party debates\n|image         = \n|order         = Fifth Democratic debate\n|host          = [[MSNBC]]<br />''[[The Washington Post]]''\n|date          = November 20, 2019\n|venue         =Oprah Winfrey Soundstage 1,<ref name=\"D5location\" /><br />Van Horn Rd,<ref>{{cite AV media |date=November 4, 2019 |title=Oprah Winfrey Sound Stage at Tyler Perry Studios will host November Democratic debate in Atlanta |medium=Video clip |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bzy22tRDbP0 |access-date=November 14, 2019 |location=Tyler Perry Studios (Van Horn Rd) |publisher=Youtube}}</ref><br />[[Tyler Perry Studios]]\n|location      = [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]\n|leadmoderator = \n|othermoderators = [[Rachel Maddow]]<br />[[Andrea Mitchell]]<br />[[Kristen Welker]]<br />[[Ashley Parker]]<ref name=\"nbcoct23\" />\n}}\n\nThe '''Democratic Party's fifth presidential debate''' was held on November 20, 2019 from 9 to 11:20&nbsp;p.m. ET,<ref name=\"nbcoct23\" /> at [[Tyler Perry Studios]] in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/breaking-georgia-host-next-democratic-debate/l34ozoORYdlqpwa2HflOkL/amp.html |title=BREAKING: Georgia to host November presidential debate |author=Greg Bluestein |date=October 8, 2019 |work=[[Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/464920-fifth-dnc-debate-to-be-held-nov-20-in-georgia?amp=1&amp_recirculation=1 |title=Fifth DNC debate to be held Nov. 20 in Georgia |author=Rachel Frazin |date=October 8, 2019 |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]}}</ref><ref name=\"ajc \"/> It was moderated by [[Rachel Maddow]], [[Andrea Mitchell]], [[Kristen Welker]] and [[Ashley Parker]].<ref name=\"nbcoct23 \"/>\n\nThe candidates who qualified were Biden, Booker, Buttigieg, Gabbard, Harris, Klobuchar, Sanders, Steyer, Warren and Yang.<ref name=\"Fifthlineup \"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display:inline-table;line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! Candidates\n!Airtime (min.)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/11/20/us/elections/debate-speaking-time.html |title=Live Tracking Each Candidate's Speaking Time in the Democratic Debate |last=Cai |first=Weiyi |date=November 20, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=November 20, 2019 |last2=Lee |first2=Jasmine C. |last3=Patel |first3=Jugal K.}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Elizabeth Warren|Warren]]\n|13.5\n|-\n|[[Pete Buttigieg|Buttigieg]]\n|12.9\n|-\n|[[Joe Biden|Biden]]\n|12.8\n|-\n|[[Bernie Sanders|Sanders]]\n|11.8\n|-\n|[[Cory Booker|Booker]]\n|11.5\n|-\n|[[Kamala Harris|Harris]]\n|11.5\n|-\n|[[Amy Klobuchar|Klobuchar]]\n|11.0\n|-\n|[[Tulsi Gabbard|Gabbard]]\n|9.2\n|-\n|[[Tom Steyer|Steyer]]\n|8.4\n|-\n|[[Andrew Yang|Yang]]\n|6.8\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Sixth debate (December 19, 2019) ===\n==== Qualification ====\nA memo released by the DNC on October 25 indicated that the qualification period for the December debate started on October 16, and ended on December 12. To qualify in terms of polling, candidates had to reach four percent or more in four polls approved by the DNC. Alternatively, reaching six percent or more in two DNC-approved polls conducted in Iowa, New Hampshire, Nevada, or South Carolina was also accepted as meeting the polling threshold. To qualify in terms of donors, candidates had to receive donations from 200,000 unique donors with 800 unique donors in 20 different states, territories or the District of Columbia.<ref name=\"poloct25\">{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/10/25/dnc-raises-thresholds-for-december-debate-000297 |title=DNC raises thresholds for December debate |last=Montellaro |first=Zach |date=October 25, 2019 |work=[[Politico]] |access-date=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\";\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\" |Qualification requirements for the sixth debate<ref name=\"poloct25 \"/>\n|-\n|'''Four-Poll Threshold'''\n|A candidate needed at '''least four percent support''' in '''four different polls''' published from a list of approved pollsters between October 16 and December 12, which could not be based on open-ended questions and covered either the national level or one of the first four primary/caucus states (Iowa, New Hampshire, Nevada, and South Carolina). Only one poll from each approved pollster counted towards meeting the threshold for each region. The approved pollsters were the [[Associated Press]], [[ABC News]]/''[[The Washington Post]]'', [[CBS News]]/[[YouGov]], [[CNN]], ''[[The Des Moines Register]]'', [[Fox News]], [[Monmouth University Polling Institute|Monmouth University]], [[National Public Radio]], [[NBC News]]/''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', [[NBC News]]/[[Marist Poll|Marist]], ''The Nevada Independent'',<ref name=\"NevIndDNC\" /> ''[[The New York Times]]'', [[Quinnipiac University Polling Institute|Quinnipiac University]], the [[University of New Hampshire]], ''[[USA Today]]''/[[Suffolk University Political Research Center|Suffolk]], and [[Winthrop University]]. For organizations that appear in pairs with other entities, only polls conducted by the listed pairings were permitted.  Organizations listed individually could partner with any other entity or field polls independently.\n|-\n|'''Early State Polling Threshold'''\n|Alternatively to the four-poll threshold, a candidate qualified with at '''least six percent support''' in any '''two polls''' from the same list of organizations and time period.  This threshold did not require that different organizations or regions be used, but did not include national polls.\n|-\n|'''Fundraising criterion'''\n|By the December 12 deadline, a candidate needed to receive financial support from a minimum of 200,000 unique donors, with at least 800 unique donors per state in at least 20 states.\n|}\n\n<!--Table has presorted the candidates by this order:\n(1) All criteria met.\n(2) Polling criterion met.\n(3) Donor criterion met.\n(4) No criteria met.\n* and they are further presorted within these 4 categories by polling average & polls-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:95%;line-height:16px;\"\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"color:black; vertical-align:top; text-align:center; background-color:#B0E2FF;\" class=\"table-no\"|'''Qualified candidates for the sixth debate'''\n|-\n! Candidate\n! Met donor criterion<br />\n! Met four-poll criterion<br />{{small|(as of December 13)<ref name=\"pollingdata6\">{{cite web |last1=Montellaro |first1=Zach |title=2020 Democratic polls |url=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1dHSFg0jrAeIAqDlFZqAu-5N2x-wk8PT-6H4DbCendUM/edit#gid=1424726684 |type=Google Sheets |work=[[Politico]] |access-date=December 13, 2019}}</ref>}}\n! Met early state polling criterion<br />{{small|(as of December 13)<ref name=\"pollingdata6\" />}}\n! Qualified for debate\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Additional<br />Ref(s)\n|-\n| [[Joe Biden|Biden]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by July 3)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|36.25}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(15 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| <ref name=\"CNN\" /><ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Bernie Sanders|Sanders]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by February 20)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|21.75}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(15 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" /><ref name=\"auto35\" />\n|-\n| [[Elizabeth Warren|Warren]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by July 8)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(22 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|26.25}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(15 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" />\n|-\n| [[Pete Buttigieg|Buttigieg]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by July 1)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(21 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|21.75}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(14 qualifying polls)}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| <ref name=\"HillJuly30\" /><ref name=\"politicooct29\">{{cite web |author1=Trent Spiner |author2=Zach Montellaro |title=Sanders leads, Biden slumps in N.H. poll |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/10/29/bernie-sanders-joe-biden-new-hampshire-poll-061068 |work=[[Politico]] |access-date=December 20, 2019 |date=October 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Amy Klobuchar|Klobuchar]]\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(by October 26)}}\n| {{Yes}}<br />{{small|(8 qualifying polls)}}{{hs|5.25}}\n| {{No}}<br />