ode/2up |year=1947 |publisher=The Manager, Government of India Press}}\n*{{cite book |last=Rezavi |first=S. Ali Nadeem |title=Exploring Mughal Gardens at Fathpur Sikri |url=https://archive.org/stream/ExploringMughalGardensAtFathpurSikri/MughalGardens#page/n1/mode/2up |year=1998 |publisher=Indian History Congress}}\n*{{cite book |last=Petruccioli |first=Attilio |title=Fatehpur Sikri |year=1992 |publisher=Ernst & Sohn}}\n*{{cite book |last=Rizvi |first=Athar Abbas |title=Fatehpur Sikri (World heritage series) |year=2002 |publisher=Archaeological Survey of India |isbn=81-87780-09-6}}\n*{{cite book |last=Rezavi |first=Syed Ali Nadeem |title=\"Iranian Influence on Medieval Indian Architecture\", The Growth of Civilizations in India and Iran |url=https://archive.org/stream/iranianInfluenceOnMedievalIndianArchitectureTheGrowthOf/IranianIndianArchitecture#page/n1/mode/2up |year=2002 |publisher=Tulika}}\n*{{cite book |last=Jain |first=Kulbhushan |title=Fatehpur Sikri: where spaces touch perfection |year=2003 |publisher=VDG |isbn=3-89739-363-8}}\n*{{cite book |last= Rezavi |first=Dr. Syed Ali Nadeem |title=Religious Disputation and Imperial Ideology: The Purpose and Location of Akbar's Ibadatkhana |url=https://archive.org/stream/ReligiousDisputationAndImperialIdeologyThePurposeAndLocationOf/Ibadatkhana#page/n0/mode/2up |year=2008 |publisher=SAGE Publications}}\n*{{cite book |last=Havell |first=E. B. |authorlink=Ernest Binfield Havell |title=A handbook to Agra and the Taj, Sikandra, Fatehpur-Sikri and the neighbourhood (1904) |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924024120200#page/n11/mode/2up |year=1904 |publisher=Longmans, Greens & Co., London |ref=Ha}}\n*{{cite book |last=Smith |first=Vincent Arthur |authorlink=Vincent Arthur Smith |title=Akbar the Great Mogul, 1542-1605 |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924024056503#page/n7/mode/2up |year=1917 |publisher=Oxford at The Clarendon Press |ref=Sm}}\n* {{cite book |last=Asher |first=Catherine Ella Blanshard |title=Architecture o